  "description": "Solomon with strandTune at 4.0 semitones — Ring A at the root, Ring B at the major third. The two-ring architecture gives each interval its own internal coupling phase, and the cross-ring link (0.3) creates a gravitational connection between root and third. macroKnot=0.5 bleeds Trefoil directionality into the Solomon matrix — one ring acquires asymmetric writhe while the other remains doubly-linked. A major third chord where the harmonic geometry is lopsided in a mathematically precise way. Very slow LFO at 0.02 Hz on braid depth: topology breathes once every 50 seconds.",
